   3.52019380368334*^9, 3.5201938262811832`*^9}, 3.520193871029818*^9, {
   3.520193905895336*^9, 3.520194085861354*^9}, {3.5201941945748587`*^9, 
   3.520194528088182*^9}, {3.520194794893856*^9, 3.520194796101344*^9}, {
   3.520194826411353*^9, 3.520195076857901*^9}, {3.520195856752646*^9, 
   3.520195859404821*^9}, {3.520198230238052*^9, 3.520198230238205*^9}, {
   3.520623873265625*^9, 3.52062387340625*^9}, {3.5208533799157925`*^9, 
   3.5208533876672363`*^9}, 3.5208534993086214`*^9},
 CellID->650705515],

Cell["\<\
\[Bullet] The green arrows are the positive sequence.\
\>", "ManipulateCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.35696210375764*^9, {3.5206187145625*^9, 3.5206187353125*^9}, {
   3.520622815100293*^9, 3.5206228155736637`*^9}, {3.520623866484375*^9, 
   3.52062386659375*^9}, {3.5208533947496414`*^9, 3.5208534029551105`*^9}},
 CellID->529057542],

Cell["\<\
\[Bullet] The blue and yellow arrows are the negative sequence, which is \
shown twice to show (1) symmetry (yellow); and (2) that the sum of its \
components is the original vector (blue).\
\>", "ManipulateCaption",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.35696210375764*^9, {3.520618735828125*^9, 3.520618755328125*^9}, {
